# gerrit-to-platform config template (epic 1fa8 / story S3 / ADR-0022).
#
# Rendered to /var/gerrit/.config/gerrit_to_platform/gerrit_to_platform.ini by
# infra/gerrit/materialize-g2p-config.sh, which substitutes the GitHub PAT into the
# `token` line below from SSM BEFORE Gerrit boots (fail-closed). The rendered file is
# mode 0600 — it holds the PAT. (The placeholder token is intentionally NOT spelled out
# in this comment: the materialiser does a global placeholder->PAT replace, so any second
# occurrence would leak the secret into the rendered comment.) g2p also reads
# replication.config from this same dir to discover the GitHub owner/repo to
# workflow_dispatch; materialize-g2p-config.sh copies it alongside.
#
# The `recheck` comment ChatOps maps to the `verify` workflow filter — a `recheck`
# comment on a change re-dispatches .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml (re-run policy).
#
# ── Branch-filtering / feature-branch dispatch spec (epic 88ab / S3, VERIFIED) ─────────
# g2p does NOT branch-filter dispatch. `patchset-created` on ANY target branch (incl.
# refs/heads/feature/*) dispatches the mapped `verify` workflow: the event→workflow mapping
# is filename-substring based (a workflow is selected iff its filename contains the search
# filter `verify` AND the literal `gerrit`), with NO branch/ref allowlist and no branch key
# in THIS ini (only `[mapping "..."]` sections exist). Source (lfit/releng-gerrit_to_platform
# @44d5d46): patchset_created.py (unconditional find_and_dispatch(project,"verify",inputs)),
# github.py filter_workflows/filter_path (branch-agnostic), config.py (no [filters] schema).
#
# HOWEVER g2p dispatches via GitHub `workflow_dispatch(ref = refs/heads/{GERRIT_BRANCH})`
# (helpers.py; github.py dispatch_workflow), and workflow_dispatch REQUIRES that ref to EXIST
# on the GitHub mirror to resolve the workflow file. Therefore feature/* changes get CI ONLY
# IF refs/heads/feature/* is replicated to the mirror — see the `push = refs/heads/feature/*`
# line in replication.config (without it a feature change 422s → no Verified; verified live:
# change 198 pre-fix got LLM-Review but no CI; change 200 post-fix dispatched CI). GERRIT_REFSPEC
# is computed as refs/changes/NN/NNNN/P (g2p helpers.py get_change_refspec — EXTERNAL g2p
# source, not an in-repo symbol) IDENTICALLY for merge and normal commits, so a merge change's
# patchset ref (which in Gerrit IS the merge tree) is what CI checks out — no special merge
# handling needed.
#
# ORDERING HAZARD (replication lag): a feature branch's FIRST patchset can lose a race — if a
# change is pushed before the replication plugin has pushed the newly-created feature branch to
# the mirror, that first workflow_dispatch 422s. Mitigation: create the feature branch and let
# it replicate (near-real-time) BEFORE pushing story changes; the `recheck` ChatOps below is the
# fallback (re-dispatch once the ref exists). NOTE: replicating feature/* also makes the mirror's
# push-triggered workflows (test/eval/optionality, on push:branches:["**"]) fan out on feature
# pushes — tracked as follow-up fern-belief-gap; those runs cast no Verified and don't affect the gate.
[mapping "comment-added"]
	recheck = verify
[github.com]
	token = __GITHUB_PAT__
